file.name: cuckoo_sandbox.yaml
file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        task_id: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        task_id: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        analysis_link: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        task_added_on: {type: string}
        task_category: {type: string}
        task_completed_on: {type: string}
        task_custom: {type: string}
        task_enforce_timeout: {type: string}
        task_errors: {type: string}
        task_id: {type: string}
        task_machine: {type: string}
        task_memory: {type: string}
        task_options: {type: string}
        task_owner: {type: string}
        task_package: {type: string}
        task_platform: {type: string}
        task_priority: {type: string}
        task_sample_id: {type: string}
        task_status: {type: string}
        task_tags: {type: string}
        task_target: {type: string}
        task_timeout: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp5:
      properties:
        category: {type: string}
        json: {type: string}
        machine_name: {type: string}
        score: {type: string}
        status: {type: string}
        task_end: {type: string}
        task_start: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes:
    BasicAuth: {scheme: basic, type: http}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Cuckoo Cuckoo Sandbox
  title: Cuckoo Cuckoo Sandbox
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Adds a File to the list of pending tasks to be processed and analyzed.
      parameters:
      - description: The File to submit to Cuckoo for analysis
        example: malware.exe
        in: query
        name: file
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cuckoo Analyze File
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Adds a URL to the list of pending tasks to be processed and analyzed.
      parameters:
      - description: The URL to submit to Cuckoo for analysis
        example: http://google.com
        in: query
        name: URL
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cuckoo Analyze URL
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Returns the full task report generated out of the analysis of the
        task associated with the specified ID
      parameters:
      - description: The Task ID of the Report Returned
        example: '13'
        in: body
        name: Task ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cuckoo Full Task Report
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Returns the analysis summary link.
      parameters:
      - description: The Task ID of the Report Returned
        example: '13'
        in: body
        name: Task ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: UI Host address
        example: https://10.20.10.10:8000
        in: query
        name: UI Host
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cuckoo Get Analysis Summary Link
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Returns the task summary.
      parameters:
      - description: The Task ID of the Report Returned
        example: '13'
        in: body
        name: Task ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cuckoo Task Status
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Returns the report summary generated out of the analysis of the
        task associated with the specified ID
      parameters:
      - description: The Task ID of the Report Returned
        example: '13'
        in: body
        name: Task ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp5'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cuckoo Report Summary
tags:
- {name: Investigation}
